What you need to know:

Kane has reportedly told Spurs he wants to leave at the end of the season and the England captain has been linked with City, Manchester United and ChelseaKane has now raised the prospect of a move to Pep Guardiola's title winners, naming City's De Bruyne as a perfect team-mateKane has scored 165 Premier League goals, 95 behind all-time top scorer Alan Shearer, and he wants to topple the former Blackburn and Newcastle striker